717820f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 212th Street
717820f-a.text:
A caretaker's house in Isham Park, Broadway, west side, opposite
212th Street.
June 8, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

717821f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 212th Street (West)
717821f-a.text:
Broadway (right), southwest from West 212th Street, showing a west-
ward view to the JJersey Palisades, as .seen through the Dyckman Street
Rap, between what is now Tryon (left) and Inwood (right) Parks. Con-
vergence in the foreground is that of West 211th and Isham Streets.
Shown on the left and with a flag atop, is an old school at the S.E.
corner of Broadway and Academy Street. Opposite same and towards the
center is the old Dyckman Farmhouse, which, is today located in Dyckman
House Park, at the N.W. corner of West 204th Street. The 3-storied,
square frame structure to the right of the latter is No. 54-56 Cooper
Street, which still stood in 1927, though surrounded by apartment
buildings.
About 1910.
Brown Brothers.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
